RAI - Market Data & News
RAI - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

Reynolds American Inc (RAI) traded on unusually high volume on Jul. 21, as the stock 
gained 0.89% to close at $66.89. On the day, Reynolds American Inc saw 16.05 million shares trade hands on 59,346 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 6.2 million shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $67.81 and $43.38 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $65.62, and its 200-day SMA $59.14. Reynolds American Inc 
has a P/B ratio of 4.4. It also has a P/E ratio of 28.5.  


Reynolds American Inc is a manufacturer of cigarettes and other tobacco related products in the United States. It offers product under the various brand which include Camel, Pall Mall, Winston and among others.

Headquartered in Winston-Salem, NC, Reynolds American Inc has 5,550 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO Debra A. Crew.


